Package: openstockflow
Type: Package
Title: Categorical Stock-Flow Modeling with Compositional Diagrams
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ian", "Moran", email = "your.email@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Implements categorical stock-flow modeling using decorated cospans
    and functorial semantics. Enables compositional model building where complex
    systems are assembled from simpler components through categorical operations.
    Supports stratification via pullbacks (e.g., by age, sex, risk group),
    ODE generation, and integration with tidyverse/tidygraph ecosystem.
    Based on the mathematical framework described in Baez et al. (2022).
License: MIT + file LICENSE
